OL,3,CGovernment rejects claim Post Office
OL,4,Ccompensation stalled ahead of election
OL,6,FThe Government has denied claims by
OL,7,Fthe former Post Office chairman that
OL,8,Fhe was told by a senior civil servant
OL,9,Fto "stall" spending on compensation to
OL,10,Fsubpostmasters ahead of the next
OL,11,Fgeneral election.
OL,13,FHenry Staunton left the role last
OL,14,Fmonth after Business Secretary Kemi
OL,15,FBadenoch said there was a need for
OL,16,F"new leadership" to fully address the
OL,17,FHorizon IT scandal that saw hundreds
OL,18,Fof former Post Office employees
OL,19,Fwrongfully prosecuted.
